<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="260" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20/831a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>)<note n="69" xml:id="d260fn69">The same telegram was sent, April 3, to the
                                    Ambassador in France (No. 117), and in the United Kingdom (No.
                                    77); on the following day a similar telegram was sent to the
                                    Chargé in the Soviet Union (No. 74).</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-03T19:00:00-05:00">April 3, 1935—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>25. I should appreciate receiving for my confidential information
                                your personal estimate of the political situation in Europe at the
                                present time and of probable developments as you foresee them.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>